data.title: In Royal Circles
data.meta_description: Royal Trips: British Prince In Turkey; Swedish King In The U.S.
data.text:
Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall, and Britain's Prince Charles, tour the Eyup Sultan Mosque during a four-day tour of Turkey on Wednesday, Nov. 28, 2007, in Istanbul. The royal couple's tour took in many historic and cultural sites.

Britain's Prince Charles and his wife Camilla, the Duchess of Cornwall, are escorted by Turkish imams as they visit the Ottoman-era Eyup Sultan Mosque in Istanbul, Turkey, Wednesday, Nov. 28, 2007. The British heir and his wife were on a four-day tour of historic sites in Turkey.

Britain's Prince Charles listens to Turkish imams as he visits the Ottoman-era Eyup Sultan Mosque in Istanbul, Turkey, Wednesday, Nov. 28, 2007.

Prince Charles gives a speech on corporate social responsibility at the Koc Museum during a four-day tour of Turkey on Wednesday, Nov. 28, 2007 in Istanbul.

Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall, smiles as she gets in her car after attending a wreath laying at the Anitkabir (memorial Tomb) of the founder of modern Turkey, Mustafa Kemal Attaturk, during a four-day tour of Turkey on Nov. 28, 2007, in Ankara.

Sweden

Sweden's Princess Madeleine, Duchess of Halsingland and Gastrikland, second from left, attends the Swedish Embassy reception for the Children First! Initiative Nov. 6, 2007, in Washington.

King Carl XVI Gustaf of Sweden speaks during a climate change seminar at the National Press Club Nov. 9, 2007, in Washington. The king joined industry leaders to speak about steps they are taking and think need to be taken to protect against climate change.

Queen Silvia of Sweden attends the World Childhood Foundation USA Gala at 583 Park Avenue in New York on Nov. 12, 2007.

Princess Madeleine, Duchess of Halsingland and Gastrikland listens to guests at a Swedish Embassy-hosted reception for the Children First! Initiative Nov. 6, 2007, in Washington.

Princess Madeleine of Sweden and her mother, Queen Silvia, attend the World Childhood Foundation USA Gala at 583 Park Avenue in New York on Nov. 12, 2007.

King Carl XVI Gustaf of Sweden, left, listens to a staff member during a climate change seminar at the National Press Club Nov. 9, 2007, in Washington.

Belgium

The Belgian royal family attends the Te Deum at the Cathedrale St. Gdule, on Kings Day on Nov. 15, 2007, in Brussels. From left are Prince Lorent, Princess Claire, Princess Mathilde, Prince Philippe, Queen Fabiola, Princess Astrid and Prince Lorentz.

Crown Princess Mathilde, left, and Crown Prince Philippe of Belgium, right, escort Queen Fabiola from the cathedral after attending the Te Deum on Kings Day on Nov. 15, 2007, in Brussels.

Princess Astrid of Belgium, second from right, along with her husband Prince Lorenz, right, mingles with the crowd at the cathedral in Brussels, Thursday Nov. 15, 2007, after celebrating King's Day. An annual event, King's Day honors the Belgian royal family.

Princess Claire of Belgium greets the crowd near the cathedral after attending the Te Deum service on Kings Day, Nov. 15, 2007, in Brussels.

Crown Princess Mathilde of Belgium greets the crowd near the cathedral after attending the Te Deum service on Kings Day, Nov. 15, 2007, in Brussels.

Jordan

Queen Rania, left, of Jordan, and Princess Firyal of Jordan arrive for the Global Leadership Award Dinner, Thursday, Oct. 25, 2007, in New York. Queen Rania was honored with the Global Humanitarian Action Award for her philanthropic efforts.

Queen Rania of Jordan tours an official school after taking part in a youth forum organized by the United Nations Foundation and UNICEF on Oct. 31, 2007, in Amman, Jordan.

Spain

Romanian President Traian Basescu and his wife are flanked by members of Spain's royal family during the royal dinner in his honor at the Royal Palace on Nov. 26, 2007, in Madrid. From left are Crown Prince Felipe, Queen Sofia, the Basescus, King Juan Carlos and Crown Princess Letizia.

Crown Princess Letizia and Crown Prince Felipe pose together at a gala dinner in honor Romanian President Traian Basescu, not seen, at the Royal Palace in Madrid, Monday, Nov. 26, 2007.
